_Pe’al_ Infinitive for regular shorushim:
The [[{{_pe’al_ infinitive}} form]] has the following conjugation pattern for [[regular shorushim]]:
| ‎לְמִכְתְּבָא‎, לְמִכְתַּב <br> _l'michtav, l'micht'vau_ <br> to write |
- The Aramaic of the Gemara is not vowelized, and so attempts to vowelize it are speculative. These conjugations are based on R Yitzchok Frank's _Grammar for Gemara_.
- The _pe’al_ infinitive form corresponds to the [[_pa’al_ infinitive]] of Hebrew.
